definition.value: The anterior abdominal wall is sunken and presents a concave rather than a convex contour.
Bleeding in the thalamus.
A deviation from normal of the mean corpuscular volume, or mean cell volume (MCV) of red blood cells, usually taken to be 80 to 100 femtoliters.
A reduction from normal of the mean corpuscular volume, or mean cell volume (MCV) of red blood cells (usually defined as an MCV below 80 femtoliters).
Strabismus in which the angle of deviation of the squiting eye remains the same in relation to the other eye, in all directions of gaze, and whichever eye is fixing.
Direction of the U wave opposite to the T wave (i.e., below baseline) in leads with upright T waves.
Increased amplitude of the U wave, defined as an amplitude greater than 1-2mm or 25 percent of the height of the T wave.
An anomaly of the complex formed by the Q, R, and S waves, which occur in rapid succession on the electrocardiogram.

Elevation of the voltage (height) of the QRS complex. There are several criteria in use, but the most common is the Sokolov-Lyon criterion (S wave depth in V1 + tallest R wave height in V5-V6 greater than 35 mm).
Abnormal amplitude of the QRS complex of the electrocardiogram (EKG).

Reduced amplitude (height) of the QRS complex of the electrocardiogram (EKG), defined as amplitudes of all the QRS complexes in the limb leads are less than 5 mm or amplitudes of all the QRS complexes in the precordial leads less than 10 mm.
A circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris in the parenchyma of the pancreas.
A form of hyperkeratosis characterized by thickening of the cornified layer without retained nuclei.
Inflammatory cells within the wall and ostia of the hair follicle, creating a follicular-based pustule.
Passage of many stools containing blood.
Passage of many stools containing blood and mucus.

label.value: Delayed recoil upon stretching of skin

definition.value: Area of skin requiring an increased amount of time to return to its original shape after being stretched.
Vomiting of material that is of fecal origin.
A structural anomaly of the mucous lining of the large intestine.
Diffuse hypertrophy or thickening of the stratum spinosum of the epidermis (prickle cell layer of the skin).
A retinal exudate in the area surrounding the optic nerve head.
A subretinal scar with a disc-like shape in the region of the macula.
A sudden violent, spasmodic, audible expiration of breath through the nose and mouth.
Marked, involuntary jerking of the eyelids.
Structural abnormality of the hypothalamus related to defective development.
Structural abnormality of the thalamus related to defective development.
Any structural anomaly of the hippocampus,
Structural abnormality of the hippocampus related to defective development.
Structural abnormality of the basal ganglia related to defective development.

label.value: Reduced red cell pyruvate kinase level

definition.value: Yellow/white, sharply delineated lesion, typically of inflammatory nature, involving the macula.
Decreased tolerance to sound.
Hypergranulosis is an increased thickness of the stratum granulosum.
